------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party components
------------------------------------------------------------------------

phi-crypto is a thin, security-reviewed wrapper over the following
open-source cryptographic libraries, each retaining its own copyright and
license. We NEVER hand-roll cryptography — every primitive delegates to a
mature, audited crate. The exact pinned revisions are recorded in
Cargo.lock for reproducible, verifiable builds. No affiliation or
endorsement is implied.

  - docknetwork/crypto       (github.com/docknetwork/crypto)        Apache-2.0
      bbs_plus · dock_crypto_utils · schnorr_pok  — the phi-bbs-v1
      BBS+ unlinkable selective disclosure over BLS12-381.
  - pairing_crypto           (github.com/mattrglobal/pairing_crypto) Apache-2.0
      the W3C/IRTF `bbs-2023` selective-disclosure suite (BLS12-381
      SHA-256), conformant with the official IETF/W3C test vectors.
      Native targets only.
  - blstrs · blst            (github.com/mattrglobal/blstrs ·        blstrs: MIT OR Apache-2.0
      github.com/supranational/blst)                                 blst: Apache-2.0
      — BLS12-381 backend used by pairing_crypto for the bbs-2023 suite.
  - arkworks                 (github.com/arkworks-rs)               Apache-2.0 OR MIT
      ark-bls12-381 · ark-ec · ark-ff · ark-serialize · ark-std
      — pairing-friendly curve and finite-field arithmetic.
  - RustCrypto               (github.com/RustCrypto)                Apache-2.0 OR MIT
      k256 (secp256k1) · p256 (secp256r1/P-256) · ecdsa · sha2
      · blake2 — elliptic-curve signatures and hashing.
  - subtle                   (github.com/dalek-cryptography/subtle) BSD-3-Clause
      — constant-time comparison primitives (timing side-channel
      resistance).
  - zeroize                  (github.com/RustCrypto/utils)          Apache-2.0 OR MIT
      — secure wiping of secret material after use.
  - rand · rand_core · getrandom (github.com/rust-random)          Apache-2.0 OR MIT
      — cryptographically secure randomness.
  - serde · serde_json       (github.com/serde-rs)                  Apache-2.0 OR MIT
  - base64 · hex                                                    Apache-2.0 OR MIT
      — encoding helpers (base64url for WebAuthn clientDataJSON).

Full license texts for these components are reproduced in their
respective source packages (resolved via Cargo and pinned in Cargo.lock).

The Phi-specific code — the CryptoSuite abstraction, the dual-curve DID
operations, the WebAuthn verifier, the voting nullifier/threshold-tally
primitives, and the WASM/FFI/C-ABI boundaries — is original work of
Homaan Smart Data.
